            "Contents": "Macrothrombocytopenia with mitral valve insufficiency is a rare hemorrhagic disorder due to a platelet anomaly characterized by dysfunctional platelets of abnormally large size moderate thrombocytopenia prolonged bleeding time and mild bleeding diathesis (ecchymoses and epistaxis) associated with mitral valve insufficiency."
